# Common Components (Mobile)

**Always check `components/common/` first** before creating any new UI element.

## Import Paths

Always import from the specific sub-path — never from `components/common` directly (except `commonStyles`):

| Category | Import path |
|----------|-------------|
| Buttons | `components/common/buttons` |
| Forms | `components/common/forms` |
| States | `components/common/states` |
| Cards | `components/common/cards` |
| Filters | `components/common/filters` |
| Styles / misc | `components/common` |

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — import from specific sub-path
import { PrimaryButton, SecondaryButton, DangerButton } from '../../../components/common/buttons';
import { FormField, FormButtons, FormModal } from '../../../components/common/forms';
import { LoadingState, EmptyState } from '../../../components/common/states';
import { CardMenu } from '../../../components/common/cards';
import { DropdownFilter, FilterOption } from '../../../components/common/filters';
import { commonStyles } from '../../../components/common';

// ❌ BAD — flat import from components/common
import { PrimaryButton, FormField, LoadingState } from '../../../components/common';
```

## Key Rules

1. ALL forms must use `FormButtons` and `FormField` — no inline implementations
2. Submit/Primary on **LEFT**, Cancel/Secondary on **RIGHT**
3. Always pass `isDark` prop for theme support
4. Use `DangerButton` for destructive actions (delete, remove)

For full component props reference, see `common-components-api.mdc`.
